  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-313">
    <command xml:space="preserve">u</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">High Above the Royal Aerie&#x000A;Your summoned mist both obscures you and blocks you from seeing the Royal Aerie.  But you've already memorized its layout, and how it relates to today's air currents, winds, and thermals.  Royal quarters to the north, well defended by circling Raven clan guards.  The librum to the east.  {LS DEBUG: a few other rooms.  Presumably.  Kitchen, Barracks, Chapel(?), }  In the center of the Aerie (and directly below you) is the Great Hall.&#x000A;&#x000A;Your summoned mist thins slightly, on its way back to equilibrium.&#x000A;&#x000A;closeness: 3.&#x000A;The Raven Squad pursues you determinedly through the thin mist.&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-314"/>
    </children>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-314">
    <command xml:space="preserve">d</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">You tuck in your wings and dive down towards the Aerie, thrilling to the misty wind streaming through your feathers.&#x000A;&#x000A;Great Hall Landing Cradle&#x000A;The Landing Cradle of the Great Hall spreads out over nearly a quarter of the vast building.  During your time here, you learned this was so that when a number of important guests and their retinues arrive at the same time, they can land simultaneously, instead of one after the other, which some would invariably take as meaning "in order of importance".&#x000A;&#x000A;To the north is the Royal Quarters, the Librum to the east, {other places LS DEBUG}, and as always, you can return to the skies or descend to the forest.&#x000A;&#x000A;You can see a leather rucksack (in which are a purple capsa of opening (in which is a scroll of rezrov), a gold capsa of FOO (closed), and a red capsa of BAR (closed)) and an important door here.&#x000A;&#x000A;closeness: 3.&#x000A;Your speed puts more distance between you and your pursuers, but it's not quite fast enough, or the mist isn't thick enough, or both, and your pursuers manage to keep you in sight.&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-315"/>
    </children>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-315">
    <command xml:space="preserve">d</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">You tuck in your wings and dive down into the forest below the Aerie, dodging tightly-spaced trees with acrobatic precision.&#x000A;&#x000A;In the Forest&#x000A;The trees below the Royal Aerie grow more closely together than in the rest of the forest, and include a wider variety, so that differently-colored woods could be incorporated into the buildings above.  This makes it harder to navigate down here--or it would if you weren't so amazing at navigation.&#x000A;&#x000A;Even through the mist, your sharp eyes spot a fine net, stretched between the trees.  It seems to be set to prevent anyone from coming up from the forest below.&#x000A;&#x000A;Your summoned mist thins back to equilibrium.  Still thick enough to mostly obscure you, but you'll have to be careful.&#x000A;&#x000A;closeness: 3.&#x000A;You expertly twist at breakneck speeds, weaving through three Ash trunks, over a branch, and around and behind a Redwood, where you halt, twist, and dive straight down the trunk, out of view of any stray Raven.&#x000A;&#x000A;High Above the Royal Aerie&#x000A;Your summoned mist both obscures you and blocks you from seeing the Royal Aerie.  But you've already memorized its layout, and how it relates to today's air currents, winds, and thermals.  Royal quarters to the north, well defended by circling Raven clan guards.  The librum to the east.  {LS DEBUG: a few other rooms.  Presumably.  Kitchen, Barracks, Chapel(?), }  In the center of the Aerie (and directly below you) is the Great Hall.&#x000A;&#x000A;The Raven's frustrated caws echo in the mist, and you plot a now-unseen course returning to the familiar currents above the Aerie.  In time, the woodpeckers cease their drumming, and the cawing fades as well.  Protocol would dictate that they return to guarding priority items, but increase patrols.&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-316"/>
    </children>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-316">
    <command xml:space="preserve">scenes</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">Scene 'Entire Game' playing (for 16 mins now)&#x000A;Scene 'Mist depletion' ended&#x000A;Scene 'Starting Off' ended&#x000A;Scene 'Everything Is Open' playing (for 15 mins now)&#x000A;Scene 'Momentum' ended&#x000A;Scene 'Super-momentum' playing (for 1 mins now)&#x000A;Scene 'Being Chased' ended&#x000A;Scene 'Not Recovering' playing (for 13 mins now)&#x000A;(Scene monitoring now switched on. Type "scenes off" to switch it off again.)&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-317"/>
    </children>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-317">
    <command xml:space="preserve">u</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">You're already high enough to avoid being seen from below; there's no need to go higher.&#x000A;&#x000A;[Scene 'Super-momentum' ends]&#x000A;[Scene 'Momentum' begins]&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
