  <item nodeId="node-351">
    <command xml:space="preserve">u</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">High Above the Royal Aerie&#x000A;Your summoned mist both obscures you and blocks you from seeing the Royal Aerie.  But you've already memorized its layout, and how it relates to today's air currents, winds, and thermals.  Royal quarters to the north, well defended by circling Raven clan guards.  The librum to the east.  {LS DEBUG: a few other rooms.  Presumably.  Kitchen, Barracks, Chapel(?), }  In the center of the Aerie (and directly below you) is the Great Hall.&#x000A;&#x000A;The Raven Squad pursues you determinedly through the mist.&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-352"/>
    </children>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-352">
    <command xml:space="preserve">summon mist</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">You draw even more moisture into the air, and feed it into the mist.  As it thickens, you feel safer, as you always do in the midst of clouds.&#x000A;&#x000A;The guards charge, but you manage to evade their uncoordinated attack.&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-353"/>
    </children>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-353">
    <command xml:space="preserve">e</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">You tuck in your wings and dive down towards the Aerie, thrilling to the misty wind streaming through your feathers.&#x000A;&#x000A;Librum Landing Cradle&#x000A;The Landing Cradle of the Librum is beautifully set with interlocking redwood and pine, suggesting shelves of books.  {Probably be more descriptive here LS DEBUG}.&#x000A;&#x000A;To the west is the Great Hall, and to the northwest is the Royal Quarters.  {also up/down}&#x000A;&#x000A;You can see Another Important Door here.&#x000A;&#x000A;Your speed puts more distance between you and your pursuers, but it's not quite fast enough, or the mist isn't thick enough, or both, and your pursuers manage to keep you in sight.&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-354"/>
    </children>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-354">
    <command xml:space="preserve">summon mist</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">You draw even more moisture into the air, and feed it into the mist.  As it thickens, you feel safer, as you always do in the midst of clouds.&#x000A;&#x000A;The guards charge, but you manage to evade their uncoordinated attack.&#x000A;&#x000A;The momentum you had from your dive wears off.  &#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-355"/>
    </children>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-355">
    <command xml:space="preserve">nw</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">Royal Landing Cradle&#x000A;It's dangerous; you can't do anything here yet. LS DEBUG.  (you can go south, southeast, up, down)&#x000A;&#x000A;The Raven Squad pursues you determinedly through the thickening mist.&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-356"/>
    </children>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-356">
    <command xml:space="preserve">summon mist</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">You draw even more moisture into the air, and feed it into the mist.  As it thickens, you feel safer, as you always do in the midst of clouds.&#x000A;&#x000A;The guards charge, but you manage to evade their uncoordinated attack.&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-357"/>
    </children>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-357">
    <command xml:space="preserve">s</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">Great Hall Landing Cradle&#x000A;The Landing Cradle of the Great Hall spreads out over nearly a quarter of the vast building.  During your time here, you learned this was so that when a number of important guests and their retinues arrive at the same time, they can land simultaneously, instead of one after the other, which some would invariably take as meaning "in order of importance".&#x000A;&#x000A;To the north is the Royal Quarters, the Librum to the east, {other places LS DEBUG}, and as always, you can return to the skies or descend to the forest.&#x000A;&#x000A;You can see a leather rucksack (in which are a purple capsa of opening (in which is a scroll of rezrov), a gold capsa of FOO (closed), and a red capsa of BAR (closed)) and an important door here.&#x000A;&#x000A;The mist is too thick for the Raven Squad to pursue you far.  You dodge around a tree, and disappear.&#x000A;The Raven's frustrated caws echo in the mist, and you plot a now-unseen course returning to the familiar currents above the Aerie.  In time, the woodpeckers cease their drumming, and the cawing fades as well.  Protocol would dictate that they return to guarding priority items, but increase patrols.&#x000A;&#x000A;High Above the Royal Aerie&#x000A;Your summoned mist both obscures you and blocks you from seeing the Royal Aerie.  But you've already memorized its layout, and how it relates to today's air currents, winds, and thermals.  Royal quarters to the north, well defended by circling Raven clan guards.  The librum to the east.  {LS DEBUG: a few other rooms.  Presumably.  Kitchen, Barracks, Chapel(?), }  In the center of the Aerie (and directly below you) is the Great Hall.&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-330">
    <command xml:space="preserve">e</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">You descend in wide circles, pulling mist down with you in what you hope is a sufficiently unsuspicious manner, trusting your memorization of the air currents to tell you where you're going...&#x000A;&#x000A;Librum Landing Cradle&#x000A;The Landing Cradle of the Librum is beautifully set with interlocking redwood and pine, suggesting shelves of books.  {Probably be more descriptive here LS DEBUG}.&#x000A;&#x000A;To the west is the Great Hall, and to the northwest is the Royal Quarters.  {also up/down}&#x000A;&#x000A;You can see Another Important Door here.&#x000A;&#x000A;closeness: 2.&#x000A;You've dived straight into a squad of Raven Guards, on their way up to accost you.  Fortunately, your speed helped you avoid most of them, but one guard's talon catches you on your side as you twist by them.&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-331"/>
    </children>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-331">
